    "value": {
      "type" : "tutorial",
      "text" : "The ^orange;Market^reset; provides a wealth of unique finds for sale to researchers and visitors alike, regardless of their affiliation. Some shopkeeps will provide quests from time to time, as well. I advise perusing every store : you never know what you'll find!"
    }
  },
  {
    "op": "add",
    "path": "/fu_useBooze",
    "value": {
      "type" : "tutorial",
      "text" : "The ^orange;Tavern^reset; provides entertainment and legal intoxicants to off-the-clock staff or visitors to the Science Outpost. While not all of us partake, some alcohol provides useful boons when ingested. After the ^orange;Tavern^reset; you'll find nothing of interest to investigate."
    }
  },
  {
    "op": "add",
    "path": "/fu_useDrugs1",
    "value": {
      "type" : "tutorial",
      "text" : "Ah, the garbage area. What else needs to be said? One thing is for certain: you most assuredly have no interest in continuing further, past the next door. Nothing of use awaits. Just turn back and do not proceed. It's better that way."
    }
  },
  {
    "op": "add",
    "path": "/fu_useDrugs2",
    "value": {
      "type" : "tutorial",
      "text" : "So...you didn't listen. No worries. Whatever you do, do not speak with the X'i over there. He is not interesting or at all worth hanging out with. Not even a little. Ignore him. He doesn't have narcotics or illegal substances."
    }
  },
  {
    "op": "add",
    "path": "/fu_useBees",
    "value": {
      "type" : "tutorial",
      "text" : "If you are an avid beekeeper, this is where you'll want to head to eschew yourself of excess Queens and Drones that do not meet your requirements. In exchange, you'll garner income and rare resources."
    }
  },
  {
    "op": "add",
